title.rendered: Preity Zinta applause Arjun Tendulkar last IPL performance over ‘Nepotism’ remarks

content.rendered:
The Mumbai Indians won over Sunrisers Hyderabad by 14-run in the IPL 2023 game on Wednesday. MI’s Arjun Tendulkar, who made his IPL debut against his Knights in Kolkata on Sunday, kept his cool and defended his 20 runs before his over in the final, wicket from Bhuvneshwar Kumar.

After taking the first wicket, Arjun spoke about his opinion of the game.

“It was great to win his first IPL wicket. I had to focus on what was at hand, on planning and execution. We planned to throw big and enable long boundaries so hitters can hit it on the longer side. (Read Also: Rinku Singh is making Hostel worth Rs.50 Lakhs for needy Cricketers)

I love bowling. I like to bowl whenever the captain asks me to, and I try to stick to my team’s schedule and do my best. We (Sachin Tendulkar and him) talk about cricket and discuss tactics before the game. I was concentrating on my clearance and bowling far enough and the line ahead. If it swings, it’s a bonus, if it doesn’t swing, it’s a bonus.”

Also, Arjun Tendulkar’s first IPL wicket was praised by former cricketers and celebrities after the match. Former cricketers like Virender Sehwag, Mohammad Kaif, and Ian Bishop have tweeted with their best regards for the young cricketer from Mumbai on his latest match performance.
